teLinkStdMIB.name: teLinkStdMIB
teLinkStdMIB.contactinfo: Martin Dubuc Email: mdubuc@ncf.ca Thomas D. Nadeau Email: tnadeau@cisco.com Jonathan P. Lang Email: jplang@ieee.org Comments about this document should be emailed directly to the MPLS working group mailing list at mpls@uu.net.
teLinkStdMIB.description: Copyright (C) 2005 The Internet Society. This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 4220; see the RFC itself for full legal notices. This MIB module contains managed object definitions for MPLS traffic engineering links as defined in 'Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering (TE)'.

TeLinkBandwidth.name: TeLinkBandwidth
TeLinkBandwidth.description: This type is used to represent link bandwidth in bps. This value is represented using a 4 octet IEEE floating point format [IEEE]. The floating point representation is not used to represent fractional value but rather to allow specification of large numbers that cannot be expressed with 32-bit integers.
TeLinkBandwidth.reference: IEEE Standard for Binary Floating-Point Arithmetic, Standard 754-1985

TeLinkPriority.name: TeLinkPriority
TeLinkPriority.description: This type is used to represent a priority. Each connection is assigned a priority. This priority is used when accounting for bandwidth on TE links or component links, for resource allocation and for rerouting purposes. Value 0 is the highest priority. Value 7 is the lowest priority.

TeLinkSwitchingCapability.name: TeLinkSwitchingCapability
TeLinkSwitchingCapability.description: Switching capability as specified in the 'OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS)' document. The values specified in this document are not contiguous.

TeLinkEncodingType.name: TeLinkEncodingType
TeLinkEncodingType.description: Link encoding type as specified in 'Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS) Signaling Functional Description' document. The values specified in this document are not contiguous.

TeLinkSonetSdhIndication.name: TeLinkSonetSdhIndication
TeLinkSonetSdhIndication.description: This convention is used to indicate whether the interface supports Standard or Arbitrary SONET/SDH. To simplify the mapping process, the values used in this textual convention match the values specified in the interface switching capability specific information field, i.e., 0 for Standard SONET/SDH and 1 for Arbitrary SONET/SDH.
TeLinkSonetSdhIndication.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203

teLinkTable.name: teLinkTable
teLinkTable.description: This table specifies the grouping of component links into TE links and the grouping of TE links into bundled links.

teLinkEntry.name: teLinkEntry
teLinkEntry.description: An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of teLink(200), i.e., for every TE link. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkEntry is created with the corresponding ifIndex. If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so is the corresponding entry in the teLinkTable. The administrative and operational status values are controlled from the ifEntry.

teLinkAddressType.name: teLinkAddressType
teLinkAddressType.description: The type of Internet address for the TE link.

teLinkLocalIpAddr.name: teLinkLocalIpAddr
teLinkLocalIpAddr.description: The local Internet address for numbered links. The type of this address is determined by the value of the teLinkAddressType object. For IPv4 and IPv6 numbered links, this object represents the local IP address associated with the TE link. For an unnumbered link, the local address is of type unknown, this object is set to the zero length string, and the teLinkOutgoingIfId object then identifies the unnumbered address. If the TE link is a Forwarding Adjacency (FA), the local IP address is set to the head-end address of the FA-LSP. If ipAddrTable is implemented, this object must have the same value as the ipAdEntAddr object that belongs to the row in ipAddrTable where ipAdEntIfIndex is equal to ifIndex.

teLinkRemoteIpAddr.name: teLinkRemoteIpAddr
teLinkRemoteIpAddr.description: The remote Internet address for numbered links. The type of this address is determined by the value of the teLinkAddressType object. The remote IP address associated with the TE link (IPv4 and IPv6 numbered links). For an unnumbered link, the remote address is of type unknown, this object is set to the zero length string, and the teLinkIncomingIfId object then identifies the unnumbered address. If the TE link is a Forwarding Adjacency, the remote IP address is set to the tail-end address of the FA-LSP.

teLinkMetric.name: teLinkMetric
teLinkMetric.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering (TE), RFC 4201
teLinkMetric.description: The traffic engineering metric for the TE link is derived from its component links. All component links within the TE link must have the same traffic engineering metric.

teLinkMaximumReservableBandwidth.name: teLinkMaximumReservableBandwidth
teLinkMaximumReservableBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkMaximumReservableBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the maximum reservable bandwidth on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum reservable bandwidth of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkProtectionType.name: teLinkProtectionType
teLinkProtectionType.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203 and Routing Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4202
teLinkProtectionType.description: This attribute specifies the link protection type of the TE link. Descriptions of the different protection types can be found in the 'Routing Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS)' document.

teLinkWorkingPriority.name: teLinkWorkingPriority
teLinkWorkingPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkWorkingPriority.description: This object represents a priority value such that a new connection with a higher priority, i.e., numerically lower than this value, is guaranteed to be setup on a primary link and not on a secondary link.

teLinkResourceClass.name: teLinkResourceClass
teLinkResourceClass.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering (TE), RFC 4201 and Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630
teLinkResourceClass.description: This attribute specifies the TE link resource class. The resource class is a 32 bit bitfield. The resource class for a link bundle is derived from the resource class of its TE links. All TE links within a link bundle must have the same resource class. Encoding of the resource class is described in the 'Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2' document.

teLinkIncomingIfId.name: teLinkIncomingIfId
teLinkIncomingIfId.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering (TE), RFC 4201
teLinkIncomingIfId.description: For unnumbered links, the incoming interface is set to the outgoing interface identifier chosen by the neighboring LSR for the reverse link corresponding to this TE link. If the link is numbered, the value of this object is 0 and the address is stored in the teLinkRemoteIpAddr instead.

teLinkOutgoingIfId.name: teLinkOutgoingIfId
teLinkOutgoingIfId.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering (TE), RFC 4201
teLinkOutgoingIfId.description: If the link is unnumbered, the outgoing interface identifier is set to the outgoing interface identifier chosen for the TE link by the advertising LSR. If the link is numbered, the value of this object is 0 and the address is stored in the teLinkLocalIpAddr instead.

teLinkRowStatus.name: teLinkRowStatus
teLinkRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. None of the writable objects in a row can be changed if status is active(1).

teLinkStorageType.name: teLinkStorageType
teLinkStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

teLinkDescriptorTable.name: teLinkDescriptorTable
teLinkDescriptorTable.description: This table specifies the interface switching capability descriptors associated with the TE links.

teLinkDescriptorEntry.name: teLinkDescriptorEntry
teLinkDescriptorEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every TE link interface switching capability descriptor. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkDescriptorEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifType of ifEntry must be teLink(200). If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all of the entries in the teLinkDescriptorTable that use the ifIndex of this TE link.

teLinkDescriptorId.name: teLinkDescriptorId
teLinkDescriptorId.description: This object specifies the link descriptor identifier.

teLinkDescrSwitchingCapability.name: teLinkDescrSwitchingCapability
teLinkDescrSwitchingCapability.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrSwitchingCapability.description: This attribute specifies interface switching capability of the TE link, which is derived from its component links.

teLinkDescrEncodingType.name: teLinkDescrEncodingType
teLinkDescrEncodingType.reference: Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS) Signaling Functional Description, RFC 3471
teLinkDescrEncodingType.description: This attribute specifies the TE link encoding type.

teLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth.name: teLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth
teLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the minimum LSP bandwidth on the TE link. This is derived from the union of the minimum LSP bandwidth of all the component links associated with the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0.name: teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 0 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 0 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio1.name: teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio1
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio1.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio1.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 1 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 1 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio2.name: teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio2
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio2.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio2.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 2 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 2 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio3.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio3.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 3 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 3 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio4.name: teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio4
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio4.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio4.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 4 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 4 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio5.name: teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio5
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio5.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio5.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 5 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 5 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio6.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio6.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 6 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 6 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio7.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio7.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 7 on the TE link. This is the union of the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 7 of all the component links within the TE link that can be used to carry live traffic.

teLinkDescrIndication.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkDescrIndication.description: This attribute specifies whether this interface supports Standard or Arbitrary SONET/SDH.

teLinkDescrRowStatus.name: teLinkDescrRowStatus
teLinkDescrRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be changed if teLinkDescrRowStatus is in the active(1) state.

teLinkDescrStorageType.name: teLinkDescrStorageType
teLinkDescrStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkDescriptorTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

teLinkSrlgTable.name: teLinkSrlgTable
teLinkSrlgTable.description: This table specifies the SRLGs associated with TE links.

teLinkSrlgEntry.name: teLinkSrlgEntry
teLinkSrlgEntry.description: An entry in this table contains information about an SRLG associated with a TE link. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkSrlgEntry using the same ifIndex is created. The ifType of ifEntry must be teLink(200). If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all of the entries in the teLinkSrlgTable that use the ifIndex of this TE link.

teLinkSrlg.name: teLinkSrlg
teLinkSrlg.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
teLinkSrlg.description: This identifies an SRLG supported by the TE link. An SRLG is identified with a 32-bit number that is unique within an IGP domain. Zero is a valid SRLG number.

teLinkSrlgRowStatus.name: teLinkSrlgRowStatus
teLinkSrlgRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified if teLinkSrlgRowStatus is active(1).

teLinkSrlgStorageType.name: teLinkSrlgStorageType
teLinkSrlgStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkSrlgTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

teLinkBandwidthTable.name: teLinkBandwidthTable
teLinkBandwidthTable.description: This table specifies the priority-based bandwidth table for TE links.

teLinkBandwidthEntry.name: teLinkBandwidthEntry
teLinkBandwidthEntry.description: An entry in this table contains information about the priority-based bandwidth of TE links. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a teLinkBandwidthEntry using the same ifIndex is created. The ifType of ifEntry must be teLink(200). If a TE link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all of the entries in the teLinkBandwidthTable that use the ifIndex of this TE link.

teLinkBandwidthPriority.name: teLinkBandwidthPriority
teLinkBandwidthPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203 and Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630
teLinkBandwidthPriority.description: This attribute specifies the priority. A value of 0 is valid as specified in the 'Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2' document.

teLinkBandwidthUnreserved.name: teLinkBandwidthUnreserved
teLinkBandwidthUnreserved.reference: Link Bundling in MPLS Traffic Engineering (TE), RFC 4201
teLinkBandwidthUnreserved.description: This attribute specifies the TE link unreserved bandwidth at priority p. It is the sum of the unreserved bandwidths at priority p of all component links associated with the TE link (excluding all links that are strictly used as protecting links).

teLinkBandwidthRowStatus.name: teLinkBandwidthRowStatus
teLinkBandwidthRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified when teLinkBandwidthRowStatus is active(1).

teLinkBandwidthStorageType.name: teLinkBandwidthStorageType
teLinkBandwidthStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the teLinkBandwidthTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

componentLinkTable.name: componentLinkTable
componentLinkTable.description: This table specifies the component link parameters.

componentLinkEntry.name: componentLinkEntry
componentLinkEntry.description: An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry that represents a component link. An ifEntry must exist in the ifTable before a componentLinkEntry is created with the corresponding ifIndex. ifEntry's ifType can be of any interface type that has been defined for TE Link interworking. Examples include ATM, Frame Relay, Ethernet, etc. If an entry representing a component link is destroyed in the ifTable, then so is the corresponding entry in the componentLinkTable. The administrative and operational status values are controlled from the ifEntry.

componentLinkMaxResBandwidth.name: componentLinkMaxResBandwidth
componentLinkMaxResBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkMaxResBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the maximum reservable bandwidth on the component link.

componentLinkPreferredProtection.name: componentLinkPreferredProtection
componentLinkPreferredProtection.description: This attribute specifies whether this component link is a primary or secondary entity.

componentLinkCurrentProtection.name: componentLinkCurrentProtection
componentLinkCurrentProtection.description: This attribute specifies whether this component link is currently used as primary or secondary link.

componentLinkRowStatus.name: componentLinkRowStatus
componentLinkRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table. No read-create object can be modified when componentLinkRowStatus is active(1).

componentLinkStorageType.name: componentLinkStorageType
componentLinkStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the componentLinkTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

componentLinkDescriptorTable.name: componentLinkDescriptorTable
componentLinkDescriptorTable.description: This table specifies the interface switching capability descriptors associated with the component links.

componentLinkDescriptorEntry.name: componentLinkDescriptorEntry
componentLinkDescriptorEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every component link descriptor. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a componentLinkDescriptorEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifEntry's ifType can be of any interface type that has been defined for TE Link interworking. Examples include ATM, Frame Relay, Ethernet, etc. If a component link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all entries in the componentLinkDescriptorTable that use the ifIndex of this component link.

componentLinkDescrId.name: componentLinkDescrId
componentLinkDescrId.description: This object specifies the link descriptor identifier.

componentLinkDescrSwitchingCapability.name: componentLinkDescrSwitchingCapability
componentLinkDescrSwitchingCapability.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkDescrSwitchingCapability.description: This attribute specifies link multiplexing capabilities of the component link.

componentLinkDescrEncodingType.name: componentLinkDescrEncodingType
componentLinkDescrEncodingType.reference: Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS) Signaling Functional Description, RFC 3471
componentLinkDescrEncodingType.description: This attribute specifies the component link encoding type.

componentLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth.name: componentLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth
componentLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkDescrMinLspBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the minimum LSP bandwidth on the component link.

componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0.name: componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0
componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio0.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 0 on the component link.

componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio1.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio1.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 1 on the component link.

componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio2.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203

componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio4.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio4.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 4 on the component link.

componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio7.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkDescrMaxLspBandwidthPrio7.description: This attribute specifies the maximum LSP bandwidth at priority 7 on the component link.

componentLinkDescrInterfaceMtu.description: This attribute specifies the interface MTU for the component link descriptor.

componentLinkDescrIndication.description: This attribute specifies whether this interface supports Standard or Arbitrary SONET/SDH.

componentLinkDescrStorageType.name: componentLinkDescrStorageType
componentLinkDescrStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row in the componentLinkDescriptorTable. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar object in the row.

componentLinkBandwidthTable.name: componentLinkBandwidthTable
componentLinkBandwidthTable.description: This table specifies the priority-based bandwidth for component links.

componentLinkBandwidthEntry.name: componentLinkBandwidthEntry
componentLinkBandwidthEntry.description: An entry in this table contains information about the priority-based bandwidth on component links. An ifEntry in the ifTable must exist before a componentLinkBandwidthEntry using the same ifIndex is created. ifEntry's ifType can be of any interface type that has been defined for TE Link interworking. Examples include ATM, Frame Relay, Ethernet, etc. If a component link entry in the ifTable is destroyed, then so are all entries in the componentLinkBandwidthTable that use the ifIndex of this component link.

componentLinkBandwidthPriority.name: componentLinkBandwidthPriority
componentLinkBandwidthPriority.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203 and Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630
componentLinkBandwidthPriority.description: This attribute specifies the priority. A value of 0 is valid as specified in the 'Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2' document.

componentLinkBandwidthUnreserved.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of Generalized Multi-Protocol Label Switching (GMPLS), RFC 4203
componentLinkBandwidthUnreserved.description: This attribute specifies the component link unreserved bandwidth at priority p.
